# Text link & tertiary CTA color

Inline text buttons and hyperlink-style actions use **`#1B73E8`** (`--color-link` in `app/globals.css`).

## When to use

- `tertiary-cta` class (card footers, “walk me through…”, “What’s covered”)
- Inline text links below cards or in copy rows
- Focus rings on link buttons: `focus-visible:ring-[#1b73e8]/25` or `/30`

## Implementation

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — shared class (14px / #1B73E8 via --color-link)
<button type="button" className="tertiary-cta">…</button>

// ✅ GOOD — token / variable
className="text-[var(--color-link)]"
className="text-[#1b73e8]"

// ❌ BAD — old blue-600
className="text-blue-600"
color: #2563eb;
```

Prefer `tertiary-cta` or `var(--color-link)` over hardcoding when adding new link actions.
